ion. When order breaks down or is threatened, political power comes under threat and the cohesion of the community is also in jeopardy. In times of impending change, crisis, or disorder, special effort is required to reassure the community of the rulers ability to maintain stability. What those in power did to convince the affected communities of their qualities as rulers, that is, their representational strategies - especially in times of change - is the subject of this book, explored through examination of case studies drawn from the ancient Near East. The volume is divided into three thematic parts: "Reestablishment of Order after Major Disruption," "Changing Order from Within," and "Perceptions of a New Order."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh1 aBeaulieu, Paul-Alain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonatz, Dominik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeldman, Marian H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeldman, Marian H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeinz, Marlies, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinz, Marlies, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJahn, Brit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuhrt, Amélie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPollock, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPruzsinszky, Regine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781575065830zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uh